    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2002 BMW M3 (E46) is a pristine example of Bavarian engineering, featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with its signature individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. This collector-grade specimen has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including a rod bearing replacement and a full Double-VANOS overhaul using Beisan components. The 6-speed Getrag manual transmission shifts with clinical precision, paired with a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis is structurally immaculate, featuring proactive subframe reinforcement and a suspension geometry preserved with OEM bushings and Bilstein dampers. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the interior shows zero bolster wear, and the exterior retains its factory-original luster, free of any imperfections. This is a mechanically sorted, concours-ready icon for the serious driver.",
      "price": 48500.0,
